{"id":802585,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bruce_Swedien","text":"Bruce Swedien (April 19, 1934 \u2013 November 16, 2020) was an American audio engineer and music producer. He was known for his work with Michael Jackson and Quincy Jones.\nCareer.\nHe became known for his work in 1962 on Frankie Valli & The Four Seasons \"Big Girls Don't Cry\".\nSwedien was a five-time Grammy Award winner. He recorded, mixed, and assisted in producing the best-selling album in the world, \"Thriller\" (1982) by Michael Jackson.\nHe also recorded and mixed for jazz artists such as Count Basie, Art Blakey, Duke Ellington, Dizzy Gillespie, Benny Goodman, Lionel Hampton, Quincy Jones, Oscar Peterson, Herbie Hancock, The Second Coming, and Jeff Oster.\nDeath.\nSwedien died on November 16, 2020 at the age of 86.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Audio_engineer","surface_form":"audio engineer","offset":67},{"uri":"Record_producer","surface_form":"music producer","offset":86},{"uri":"Michael_Jackson","surface_form":"Michael Jackson","offset":133},{"uri":"Quincy_Jones","surface_form":"Quincy Jones","offset":153},{"uri":"Frankie_Valli_%26amp%3B_The_Four_Seasons","surface_form":"Frankie Valli & The Four Seasons","offset":215},{"uri":"Big_Girls_Don%27t_Cry_(The_Four_Seasons_song)","surface_form":"Big Girls Don't Cry","offset":249},{"uri":"Grammy_Award","surface_form":"Grammy Award","offset":295},{"uri":"List_of_best-selling_albums","surface_form":"best-selling album in the world","offset":366},{"uri":"Thriller_(Michael_Jackson_album)","surface_form":"Thriller","offset":400},{"uri":"Michael_Jackson","surface_form":"Michael Jackson","offset":420},{"uri":"Count_Basie","surface_form":"Count Basie","offset":489},{"uri":"Art_Blakey","surface_form":"Art Blakey","offset":502},{"uri":"Duke_Ellington","surface_form":"Duke Ellington","offset":514},{"uri":"Dizzy_Gillespie","surface_form":"Dizzy Gillespie","offset":530},{"uri":"Benny_Goodman","surface_form":"Benny Goodman","offs